CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier reads:"Shriners Spread Cheer- North Side Elks Home was the scene of the Shriners' recent Yuletide party. Left to right, Noble Stanley Banner, Noble Rev. LeRoy Patrick, Imperial Outer Guard Marshall S. Johnson, Illustrious Potentate Clarence B. Queen, Noble Taylor Thompson, publicity chairman, and Imperial Deputy of the Oasis Harry Keen."
TitMainTitle: Portrait of six Shriners wearing Sahara fezzes, including Stanley Banner, Reverend LeRoy Patrick, Marshall S. Johnson, Clarence R. Queen, Taylor Thompson and Harry Keen, with clock and framed portraits on wall in background
